obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (17051)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17051&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Essential Commodities Act, 1955.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 25 of 1968, s. 2 and the Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 15-8-1968).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (17052)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17052&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `^1[(ia) "Collector" includes an Additional Collector and such other officer, not below the rank`
  line `of Sub-Divisional Officer, as may be authorised by the Collector to perform the functions and`
  line `exercise the powers of the Collector under this Act;]`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b)"food-crops" include crops of sugarcane;`
  line
  line `(c) "notified order" means an order notified in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `^3[(cc) "order" includes a direction issued thereunder;]`
  line
  line `^4[(d) "State Government," in relation to a Union territory, means the administrator thereof;]`
  line
  line `^3[(e) "sugar" means--`
  line
  line `(i) any form of sugar containing more than ninety per cent, of sucrose, including sugar`
  line candy;
  line
  line `(ii) khandsari sugar or bura sugar or crushed sugar or any sugar in crystalline or powdered`
  line `form; or`
  line
  line `(iii) sugar in process in vacuum pan sugar factory or raw sugar produced therein.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act 10 of 1955.--In section 2 of the Essential Commodities Act, 1955 (10 of 1955), in its application to the State of Maharashtra,--`
  line
  line `(a) for clause (ia), the following clause shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(ia) "Collector" in any Rationing Area means the Controller of Rationing designated for that area and includes the Deputy or Assistant Controller or Rationing; and elsewhere, the Collector of the District and includes Additional, Deputy or Assistant Collector, Sub-Divisional Officer and District Supply Officer within his respective jurisdiction;";`
  line
  line `(b) clause (ai) shall be deleted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 6 of 2003, s. 2].`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act X of 1955.--In section 2 of the Essential Commodities Act,`
  line `1955, as amended in its application to Uttar Pradesh, hereinafter called the principal Act, before`
  line `clause (a), the following clause shall be inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `"(aa) ‘Collector’ includes such officer not below the rank of an Assistant Collector of the first`
  line `class as may be authorized by the Collector to exercise the powers conferred on him by or under`
  line `the provisions of this Act;"`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 18 of 1975, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act 10 of 1955.--In section 2 of the Essential Commodities act,`
  line `1955 (hereinafter referred to as the principal Act). Clause (aa) as inserted by the Essential`
  line `Commodities (Uttar Pradesh Amendment) Act, 1975, hereinafter referred to as the Uttar Pradesh`
  line `Amendment, shall stand omitted with effect from September 2, 1976, the date of the commencement`
  line `of the Essential Commodities (Amendment) Act, 1976, hereinafter referred to as the Central`
  line `(Amendment).`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XVI of 1978, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 92 of 1976, s. 2 (w.e.f. 2-9-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (c) omitted by Act 54 of 2006, s. 2 (w.e.f. 12-2-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 36 of 1967, s. 2 (w.e.f. 30-12-1967).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956, for clause (d).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (17053)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 3
  title `Essential commodities declaration, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 54 of 2006, s. 3 (w.e.f. 12-2-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17053&sectionno=2A&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[2A. Essential commodities declaration, etc.--(1) For the purposes of this Act, essential`
  line `commodity means a commodity specified in the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), the Central Government may, if it is satisfied that`
  line `it is necessary so to do in the public interest and for reasons to be specified in the notification`
  line `published in the Official Gazette, amend the Schedule so as to--`
  line
  line `(a) add a commodity to the said Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) remove any commodity from the said Schedule,`
  line
  line `in consultation with the State Governments.`
  line
  line `(3) Any notification issued under sub-section (2) may also direct that an entry shall be made`
  line `against such commodity in the said Schedule declaring that such commodity shall be deemed to be an`
  line `essential commodity for such period not exceeding six months to be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, in the public interest and for reasons to be specified,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, extend such period beyond the said six months.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may exercise its powers under sub-section (2) in respect of the`
  line `commodity to which Parliament has power to make laws by virtue of Entry 33 List III in the Seventh`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution.`
  line
  line `(5) Every notification issued under sub-section (2) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `issued, before both Houses of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (17054)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Powers to control production, supply, distribution, etc., of essential commodities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17054&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) If`
  line `the Central Government is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient so to do for maintaining or`
  line `increasing supplies of any essential commodity or for securing their equitable distribution and`
  line `availability at fair prices, ^1[or for securing any essential commodity for the defence of India or the`
  line `efficient conduct of military operations], it may, by order, provide for regulating or prohibiting the`
  line `production, supply and distribution thereof and trade and commerce therein.`
  line
  line ^2[*****
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the powers conferred by sub-section (1), an order made`
  line `thereunder may provide--`
  line
  line `(a) for regulating by licences, permits or otherwise the production or manufacture of`
  line `any essential commodity;`
  line
  line `(b) for bringing under cultivation any waste or arable land, whether appurtenant to a building`
  line `or not, for the growing thereon of food-crops generally or of specified food-crops, and for`
  line `otherwise maintaining or increasing the cultivation of food-crops generally, or of specified`
  line food-crops.
  line
  line `(c) for controlling the price at which any essential commodity may be bought or sold;`
  line
  line `(d) for regulating by licences, permits or otherwise the storage, transport, distribution,`
  line `disposal, acquisition, use or consumption of, any essential commodity;`
  line
  line `(e) for prohibiting the withholding from sale of any essential commodity ordinarily kept for`
  line sale;
  line
  line `^3[(f) for requiring any person holding in stock, or engaged in the production, or in the business`
  line `of buying or selling, of any essential commodity,--`
  line
  line `(a) to sell the whole or a specified part of the quantity held in stock or produced or`
  line `received by him or,`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any such commodity which is likely to be produced or received by him,`
  line `to sell the whole or a specified part of such commodity when produced or received by him,`
  line
  line `to the Central Government or a State Government or to an officer or agent of such Government or to a`
  line `Corporation owned or controlled by such Government or to such other person or class of persons and`
  line `in such circumstances as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--An order made under this clause in relation to foodgrains, edible oilseeds or`
  line `edible oils, may, having regard to the estimated production, in the concerned area, of such foodgrains,`
  line `edible oilseeds and edible oils, fix the quantity to be sold by the producers in such area and may also`
  line `fix, or provide for the fixation of, such quantity on a graded basis, having regard to the aggregate of`
  line `the area held by, or under the cultivation of, the producers.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the purpose of this clause, production with its grammatical variations and`
  line `cognate expressions includes manufacture of edible oils and sugar;]`
  line
  line `(g) for regulating or prohibiting any class of commercial or financial transactions relating to`
  line `foodstuffs ^4*** which, in the opinion of the authority making the order, are, or, if unregulated, are`
  line `likely to be, detrimental to the public interest;`
  line
  line `(h) for collecting any information or statistics with a view to regulating or prohibiting any of`
  line `the aforesaid matters;`
  line
  line `(i) for requiring persons engaged in the production, supply or distribution of or trade and`
  line `commerce in, any essential commodity to maintain and produce for inspection such books,`
  line `accounts and records relating to their business and to furnish such information relating thereto, as`
  line `may be specified in the order;`
  line
  line `^5[(ii) for the grant or issue of licences, permits or other documents, the charging of fees`
  line `therefore, the deposit of such sum, if any, as may be specified in the order as security for the due`
  line `performance of the conditions of any such licence, permit or other document, the forfeiture of the`
  line `sum so deposited or any part thereof for contravention of any such conditions, and the`
  line `adjudication of such forfeiture by such authority as may be specified in the order;]`
  line
  line `^5[(j) for any incidental and supplementary matters, including, in particular, the entry, search or`
  line `examination of premises, aircraft, vessels, vehicles or other conveyances and animals, and the`
  line `seizure by a person authorised to make such entry, search or examination,--`
  line
  line `(i) of any articles in respect of which such person has reason to believe that a`
  line `contravention of the order has been, is being, or is about to be committed and any packages,`
  line `coverings or receptacles in which such articles are found;`
  line
  line `(ii) of any aircraft, vessel, vehicle or other conveyance or animal used in carrying such`
  line `articles, if such person has reason to believe that such aircraft, vessel, vehicle or other`
  line `conveyance or animal is liable to be forfeited under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `^7[(iii) of any books of accounts and documents which in the opinion of such person, may`
  line `be useful for, or relevant to, any proceeding under this Act and the person from whose`
  line `custody such books of accounts or documents are seized shall be entitled to make copies`
  line `thereof or to take extracts therefrom in the presence of an officer having the custody of such`
  line `books of accounts or documents.]]`
  line
  line `(3) Where any person sells any essential commodity in compliance with an order made with`
  line `reference to clause (f) of sub-section (2), there shall be paid to him the price therefore as hereinafter`
  line `provided:--`
  line
  line `(a) where the price can, consistently with the controlled price, if any, fixed under this section,`
  line `be agreed upon, the agreed price;`
  line
  line `(b) where no such agreement can be reached, the price calculated with reference to the`
  line `controlled price, if any;`
  line
  line `(c) where neither clause (a) nor clause (b) applies, the price calculated at the market rate`
  line `prevailing in the locality at the date of sale.`
  line
  line `^8[(3A) (i) If the Central Government is of opinion that it is necessary so to do for controlling the`
  line `rise in prices or preventing the hoarding, of any food-stuff in any locality, it may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, direct that notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), the price at which the food-stuff shall be sold in the locality in compliance with an order made with reference to`
  line `clause (f) of sub-section (2) shall be regulated in accordance with the provisions of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(ii) Any notification issued under this sub-section shall remain in force for such period not`
  line `exceeding three months as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(iii) Where, after the issue of a notification under this sub-section, any person sells foodstuff of`
  line `the kind specified therein and in the locality so specified, in compliance with an order made with`
  line `reference to clause (f) of sub-section (2), there shall be paid to the seller as the price therefor--`
  line
  line `(a) where the price can, consistently with the controlled price of the foodstuff, if any, fixed`
  line `under this section, be agreed upon, the agreed price;`
  line
  line `(b) where no such agreement can be reached, the price calculated with reference to the`
  line `controlled price, if any;`
  line
  line `(c) where neither clause (a) nor clause (b) applies, the price calculated with reference to`
  line `average market rate prevailing in the locality during the period of three months immediately`
  line `preceding the date of the notification.`
  line
  line `(iv) For the purposes of sub-clause (c) of clause (iii), the average market rate prevailing in the`
  line `locality shall be determined by an officer authorised by the Central Government in this behalf, with`
  line `reference to the prevailing market rates for which published figures are available in respect of that`
  line `locality or of a neighbouring locality; and the average market rate so determined shall be final and`
  line `shall not be called in question in any court.]`
  line
  line `^9[(3B) Where any person is required, by an order made with reference to clause (f) of sub-section`
  line `(2), to sell to the Central Government or a State Government or to an officer or agent of such`
  line `Government or to a Corporation owned or controlled by such Government, any grade or variety of`
  line `foodgrains, edible oilseeds or edible oils in relation to which no notification has been issued under`
  line `sub-section (3A), or such notification having been issued, has ceased to be in force, there shall be paid`
  line `to the person concerned, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in sub-section (3), an`
  line `amount equal to the procurement price of such foodgrains, edible oilseeds or edible oils, as the case`
  line `may be, specified by the State Government, with the previous approval of the Central Government`
  line `having regard to--`
  line
  line `(a) the controlled price, if any, fixed under this section or by or under any other law for the`
  line `time being in force for such grade or variety of foodgrains, edible oilseeds or edible oils;`
  line
  line `(b) the general crop prospects;`
  line
  line `(c) the need for making such grade or variety of foodgrains, edible oilseeds or edible oils`
  line `available at reasonable prices to the consumers, particularly the vulnerable sections of the`
  line `consumers; and`
  line
  line `(d) the recommendations, if any, of the Agricultural Prices Commission with regard to the`
  line `price of the concerned grade or variety of foodgrains, edible oilseeds or edible oils.]`
  line
  line `^10[(3C) Where any producer is required by an order made with reference to clause (f) of subsection`
  line `(2) to sell any kind of sugar (whether to the Central Government or to a State Government or`
  line `to an officer or agent of such Government or to any other person or class of persons) whether a`
  line `notification was issued under sub-section (3A) or otherwise, then, notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in sub-section (3), there shall be paid to that producer only such amount as the Central Government`
  line `may, by order, determine, having regard to--`
  line
  line `(a) the fair and remunerative price, if any, determined by the Central Government as the price`
  line `of sugarcane to be taken into account under this section;`
  line
  line `(b) the manufacturing cost of sugar;`
  line
  line `(c) the duty or tax, if any, paid or payable thereon; and`
  line
  line `(d) a reasonable return on the capital employed in the business of manufacturing of sugar:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may determine different prices, from time to time, for`
  line `different areas or factories or varieties of sugar:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where any provisional determination of price of levy sugar has been done in`
  line `respect of sugar produced up to the sugar season 2008-2009, the final determination of price may be`
  line `undertaken in accordance with the provisions of this sub-section as it stood immediately before the 1st`
  line `day of October, 2009.`
  line
  line `Explanation ^11[I].-- For the purposes of this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "fair and remunerative price" means the price of sugarcane determined by the Central`
  line `Government under this section;`
  line
  line `(b) "manufacturing cost of sugar" means the net cost incurred on conversion of sugarcane into`
  line `sugar including net cost of transportation of sugarcane from the purchase centre to the factory`
  line `gate, to the extent it is borne by the producer;`
  line
  line `(c) "producer" means a person carrying on the business of manufacturing sugar;`
  line
  line `(d) "reasonable return on the capital employed" means the return on net fixed assets plus`
  line `working capital of a producer in relation to manufacturing of sugar including procurement of`
  line `sugarcane at a fair and remunerative price determined under this section.]`
  line
  line `^12[Explanation II.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the expressions "fair and`
  line `remunerative price" referred to in clause (a), "manufacturing cost of sugar" referred to in clause (b)`
  line `and "reasonable return on the capital employed" referred to in clause (d), of this sub-section do not`
  line `include the price paid or payable under any order or any enactment of any State Government and any`
  line `price agreed to between the producer and the grower or a sugarcane growers' co-operative society.]`
  line
  line `^13[(3D) The Central Government may direct that no producer, importer or exporter shall sell or`
  line `otherwise dispose of or deliver any kind of sugar or remove any kind of sugar from the bonded go`
  line `downs of the factory in which it is produced, whether such godowns are situated within the premises`
  line `of the factory or outside or from the warehouses of the importers or exporters, as the case may be`
  line `except under and in accordance with the direction issued by the Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not affect the pledging of such sugar by any producer or`
  line `importer in favour of any scheduled bank as defined in clause (e) of section 2 of the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) or any corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of the`
  line `Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), so, however,`
  line `that no such hank shall sell the sugar pledged to it except under and in accordance with a direction`
  line `issued by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3E) The Central Government may, from time to time, by general or special order, direct any`
  line `producer or importer or exporter or recognised dealer or any class of producers or recognised dealers,`
  line `to take action regarding production, maintenance of stocks, storage, sale, grading, packing, marking,`
  line `weighment, disposal, delivery and distribution of any kind of sugar in the manner specified in the`
  line direction.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sub-section (3D) and this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "producer" means a person carrying on the business of manufacturing sugar;`
  line
  line `(b) "recognised dealer'" means a person carrying on the business of purchasing, selling or`
  line `distributing sugar;`
  line
  line `(c) "sugar" includes plantation white sugar, raw sugar and refined sugar, whether`
  line `indigenously produced or imported.]`
  line
  line `(4) If the Central Government is of opinion that it is necessary so to do for maintaining or`
  line `increasing the production and supply of an essential commodity, it may, by order, authorize any`
  line `person (hereinafter referred to as an authorized controller) to exercise, with respect to the whole or`
  line `any part of any such undertaking engaged in the production and supply of the commodity as may be`
  line `specified in the order such functions of control as may be provided therein and so long as such order`
  line `is in force with respect to any undertaking or part thereof,--`
  line
  line `(a) the authorized controller shall exercise his functions in accordance with any instructions`
  line `given to him by the Central Government, so, however, that he shall not have any power to give`
  line `any direction inconsistent with the provisions of any enactment or any instrument determining the`
  line `functions of the persons in-charge of the management of the undertaking, except in so far as may`
  line `be specifically provided by the order; and`
  line
  line `(b) the undertaking or part shall be carried on in accordance with any directions given by the`
  line `authorised controller under the provisions of the order, and any person having any functions of`
  line `management in relation to the undertaking or part shall comply with any such directions.`
  line
  line `(5) An order made under this section shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an order of a general nature or affecting a class of persons, be notified in the`
  line `Official Gazette; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an order directed to a specified individual be served on such individual--`
  line
  line `(i) by delivering or tendering it to that individual, or`
  line
  line `(ii) if it cannot be so delivered or tendered, by affixing it on the outer door or some other`
  line `conspicuous part of the premises in which that individual lives, and a written report there of`
  line `shall be prepared and witnessed by two persons living in the neighbourhood.`
  line
  line `(6) Every order made under this section by the Central Government or by any officer or authority`
  line `of the Central Government shall be laid before both Houses of Parliament, as soon as may be, after it`
  line `is made.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3 of Act X of 1955.--In section 3 of the principal Act, in sub-section (2),`
  line `after clause (f), the following clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(ff) for preventing the hoarding of any essential commodity;"`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 9 of 1974, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3.--In section 3 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (2), for clause (f), the following clause shall be substituted and be deemed`
  line `always to have been substituted namely--`
  line
  line `"(f) for requiring any person holding in stock, or engaged in the manufacture or production of,`
  line `or in the business of buying or selling, any essential commodity to sell the whole or a specified`
  line `part of the quantity held in stock or manufactured or produced or likely to be manufactured or`
  line `produced by him or received or likely to be received by him in the course of said business of`
  line `buying or selling, to the Central Government or a State Government or to an officer or agent of`
  line `such Government or to such other person or class of person and in such circumstances as may be`
  line `specified in the order;`
  line
  line `Explanation.--An order relating to food grains made with reference to this clause,--`
  line
  line `(i) may specify the prices, fixed by the State Government in this behalf, after taking into`
  line `account the recommendations, if any, of the Agricultural Prices Commission and with the prior`
  line `concurrence of the Central Government, as the amount which shall be paid for the food grain`
  line `required to be sold under the order,`
  line
  line `(ii) may fix or provide for the fixation of the quantity to be sold by a producer with reference`
  line `to the area under cultivation and the availability of irrigation for production of the particular food`
  line `grain to which the order relates, and also fix or provide for the fixation of such quantities on a`
  line `graded basis having regard to the aggregate area held by or under the cultivation of different`
  line `producers."`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (3), for clause (c), substitute the following clauses which shall be Food`
  line `deemed always to have been substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(c) in the case of food grains, where neither clause (a) nor clause (b) applies, the price, if`
  line `any, specified in the said order;`
  line
  line `(d) where neither clause (a) nor (b), nor (c) applies, the price calculated at the market rate`
  line `prevailing in the locality at the date of sale."`
  line
  line `(c) in sub-section (3B), after clause (i), insert the following clause which shall be deemed`
  line `always to have been inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(ia) in the case of food grains, where no controlled price is fixed by an order made with`
  line `reference to clause (c) of sub-section (2), the amount specified in the said Order made with`
  line `reference to clause (f) of sub-section (2) for such grade or variety of food grains; or"`
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 18 of 1975, s. 4]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3 of Act X of 1955.--In section 3 of the Essential Commodities Act,`
  line `1955, as amended in its application to Uttar Pradesh, in sub-section (2), in clause (f), as substituted by`
  line `the Essential Commodities (Uttar Pradesh Amendment) Act, 1975, in the Explanation thereof, for`
  line `sub-clause (II), the following sub-clause shall be substituted and be deemed always to have been`
  line `substituted Namely:--`
  line
  line `"(II) may fix or provide for the fixation of the quantity to be sold by a producer with reference to`
  line `the area under cultivation for production of the particular (foodgrains to which the order relates, and`
  line `also fix or provide for the fixation of such quantities on a graded basis having regard to the aggregate`
  line `area held by or under the cultivation of different producers."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 39 of 1975, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3 of Act no. 10 of 1955.--(1) In section 3 of the principal Act, in subsection (2), clause (f), as substituted by the Uttar Pradesh Amendment read with the Essential`
  line `Commodities (Uttar Pradesh Second Amendment) Act, 1975 shall be omitted and deemed to have`
  line `been omitted with effect from the date of the commencement of the Central Amendment.`
  line
  line `(2) In the said sub-section, in clause (f), as substituted by the central Amendment, after`
  line `Explanation 1, the following Explanation shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Explanation I-A.--An order made this clause in relation to rice may, having regard to the milling`
  line `capacity of a rice mill, fix the quantity to be sold by the licensed miller and may also fix or provide`
  line `for the fixation of such quantity on a graded basis."`
  line
  line `(3) In the said section 3, sub-section (3-B), as amended by the Uttar Pradesh Amendment, shall be`
  line `committed and deemed to have been omitted with effect from the date of commencement of the`
  line `central Amendment.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XVI of 1978, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1967, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-12-1967).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section(1A) omitted by Act 40 of 2021, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-11-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 92 of 1976, s. 3, for clause (f).`
  line
  line `4. The words or cotton textiles omitted by Act 54 of 2006, s. 4 (w.e.f. 12-2-2007).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 17 of 1961, s. 2.`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 66 of 1971, s. 2, for clause (j) (w.e.f. 23-12-1971).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 92 of 1976, s. 3, for sub-clause (iii).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 13 of 1957, s. 2 (w.e.f. 4-6-1957).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 92 of 1976, s. 3, for sub-section (3B).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 36 of 2009, s. 2, for sub-section (3C) and the Explanations (w.e.f. 1-10-2009).`
  line
  line `11. The existing Explanation numbered as Explanation I by Act 35 of 2010, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-2009).`
  line
  line `12. Explanation II ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2009).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by Act 37 of 2003, s. 2 (w.e.f.14-6-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (17055)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Imposition of duties on State Governments, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17055&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `An order made under section 3 may`
  line `confer powers and impose duties upon the Central Government or the State Government or officers`
  line `and authorities of Central Government or State Government, and may contain directions to any State`
  line `Government or to officers and authorities thereof as to the exercise of any such powers or the`
  line `discharge of any such duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (17056)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 66 of 1971, s. 3, for "the power to make orders under section 3" (w.e.f. 23-12-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17056&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notified order, direct that ^1[the`
  line `power to make orders or issue notifications under section 3] shall, in relation to such matters and`
  line `subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the direction, be exercisable also by--`
  line
  line `(a) such officer or authority subordinate to the Central Government, or`
  line
  line `(b) such State Government or such officer or such authority subordinate to a State`
  line Government,
  line
  line `as may be specified in the direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (17057)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Effect of orders inconsistent with other enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17057&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Any order made under section 3 shall`
  line `have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any enactment other than`
  line `this Act or any instrument having effect by virtue of any enactment other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (17058)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 8
  title `Confiscation of essential commodity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17058&sectionno=6A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Confiscation of essential commodity.-- ^2[(1)] Where any ^3[essential commodity is`
  line `seized] in pursuance of an order made under section 3 in relation thereto, ^4[a report of such seizure shall, without unreasonable delay, be made to] the Collector of the district or the Presidency town in`
  line `which such ^5[essential commodity is seized] and whether or not a prosecution is instituted for the`
  line `contravention of such order, the Collector ^6[may, if he thinks it expedient so to do, direct the essential`
  line `commodity so seized to be produced for inspection before him, and if he is satisfied] that there has`
  line `been a contravention of the order ^7[may order confiscation of--`
  line
  line `(a) the essential commodity so seized;`
  line
  line `(b) any package, covering or receptacle in which such essential commodity is found; and`
  line
  line `(c) any animal, vehicle, vessel or other conveyance used in carrying such essential commodity:]`
  line
  line `Provided that without prejudice to any action which may be taken under any other provision of`
  line `this Act, no foodgrains or edible oilseeds in pursuance of an order made under section 3 in relation`
  line `thereto from a producer shall, if the seized foodgrains or edible oilseeds have been produced by him,`
  line `be confiscated under this section:`
  line
  line `^8[Provided further that in the case of any animal, vehicle, vessel or other conveyance used for the`
  line `carriage of goods or passengers for hire, the owner of such animal, vehicle, vessel or other`
  line `conveyance shall be given an option to pay, in lieu of its confiscation, a fine not exceeding the market`
  line `price at the date of seizure of the essential commodity sought to be carried by such animal, vehicle,`
  line `vessel or other conveyance.]`
  line
  line `^8[(2) Where the Collector, on receiving a report of seizure or on inspection of any essential`
  line `commodity under sub-section (1), is of the opinion that the essential commodity is subject to speedy`
  line `and natural decay or it is otherwise expedient in the public interest so to do, he may--`
  line
  line `(i) order the same to be sold at the controlled price, if any, fixed for such essential commodity`
  line `under this Act or under any other law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where no such price is fixed, order the same to be sold by public auction:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of foodgrains, the Collector may, for its equitable distribution and`
  line `availability at fair prices, order the same to be sold through fair price shops at the price fixed by the`
  line `Central Government or by the State Government, as the case may be, for the retail sale of such`
  line `foodgrains to the public.`
  line
  line `(3) where any essential commodity is sold, as aforesaid, the sale proceeds thereof, after deduction`
  line `of the expenses of any such sale or auction or other incidental expenses relating thereto, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) where no order or confiscation is ultimately passed by the Collector,`
  line
  line `(b) where an order passed on appeal under sub-section (1) of section 6C so requires, or`
  line
  line `(c) where in a prosecution instituted for the contravention of the order in respect of which an`
  line `order of confiscation has been made under this section, the person concerned is acquitted,`
  line
  line `be paid to the owner thereof or the person from whom it is seized.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 1966, s. 3 (w.e.f. 3-9-1966).`
  line
  line `2. Section 6A renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 92 of 1976, s. 4 (w.e.f. 2-9-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 36 of 1967, s. 4, for "foodgrains, edible oilseeds or edible oils are seized" (w.e.f. 30-12-1967).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 92 of 1976, s. 4, for "it may be produced without any unreasonable delay, before" (w.e.f. 2-9-1976).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 36 of 1967, s. 4, for food grains, edible oilseeds or edible oils are seized (w.e.f. 30-12-1967).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 92 of 1976, s. 4, for "if satisfied" (w.e.f. 2-9-1976).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 30 of 1974, s. 4, for "may order confiscation of the essential commodity so seized" (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 92 of 1976, s. 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_b:
  sectionId (17059)
  sectionNo 6B
  orderNo 9
  title `Issue of show cause notice before confiscation of food grains, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17059&sectionno=6B&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_6_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[6B. Issue of show cause notice before confiscation of food grains, etc.--^3[(1)] No order`
  line `confiscating ^4[any ^5[essential commodity] package, covering, receptacle, animal, vehicle, vessel or`
  line `other conveyance] shall be made under section 6A unless the owner of such ^2[essential`
  line `commodity] package, covering, receptacle, animal, vehicle, vessel or other conveyance) or the person`
  line `from whom ^6[it is seized]--`
  line
  line `(a) is given a notice in writing informing him of the grounds on which it is proposed to`
  line `confiscate the ^6[essential commodity] package, covering, receptacle, animal, vehicle, vessel or`
  line `other conveyance;]`
  line
  line `(b) is given an opportunity of making a presentation in wiring within such reasonable time as`
  line `may be specified in the notice against the ground of confiscation; and`
  line
  line `(c) is given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `^7[(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), no order confiscating any animal,`
  line `vehicle, vessel or other conveyance shall be made under section 6A if the owner of the animal, vehicle`
  line `vessel or other conveyance proves to the satisfaction of the Collector that it was used in carrying the`
  line `essential commodity without the knowledge or connivance of the owner himself, his agent, if any, and`
  line `the person in charge of the animal, vehicle, vessel or other conveyance and that each of them had`
  line `taken all reasonable and necessary precautions against such use.]`
  line
  line `^8[(3) No order confiscating any essential commodity package, covering, receptacle, animal,`
  line `vehicle, vessel or other conveyance shall be invalid merely by reason of any defect or irregularity in`
  line `the notice, given under clause (a) of sub-section (1), if, in giving such notice, the provisions of that`
  line `clause have been substantially complied with.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 1966, s. 3 (w.e.f. 3-9-1966).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 92 of 1976, s. 4, for "if satisfied" (w.e.f. 2-9-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Section 6B renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 30 of 1974, s. 5 (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
  line
  line `46. Subs. by Act 36 of 1967, s. 5, for "any foodgrain, edible oilseeds or edible oils" (w.e.f. 30-12-1967).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 30 of 1974, s. 5, for "essential commodity" (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 36 of 1967, s. 5, for "they are seized" (w.e.f. 30-12-1967).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 30 of 1974, s. 5 (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).)`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 92 of 1976, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-9-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_c:
  sectionId (17060)
  sectionNo 6C
  orderNo 10
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17060&sectionno=6C&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_6_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[6C. Appeal.--(1) Any person aggrieved by an order of confiscation under section 6A may,`
  line `within one month from the date of the communication to him of such order, appeal to any judicial`
  line `authority appointed by the State Government concerned and the judicial authority shall, after giving`
  line `an opportunity to the appellant to be heard, pass such order as it may think fit, confirming, modifying`
  line `or annulling the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an order under section 6A is modified or annulled by such judicial authority, or where`
  line `in a prosecution instituted for the contravention of the order in respect of which an order of`
  line `confiscation has been made under section 6A, the person concerned is acquitted, and in either case it`
  line `is not possible for any reason to ^2[return the essential commodity seized ], ^3[such persons shall, except`
  line `except as provided by sub-section (3) of section 6A, be paid] the price therefore ^4[as if the essential`
  line `commodity,] had been sold to the Government with reasonable interest calculated from the day of the`
  line `seizure of ^5[the essential commodity] ^6[and such price shall be determined--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of food grains, edible oilseeds or edible oils, in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of sub-section (3B) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of sugar, in accordance with the provisions of subsection (3C) of section 3 ;`
  line and
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of any other essential commodity, in accordance with the provisions of subsection`
  line `(3) of section 3.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 1966, s. 3 (w.e.f. 3-9-1966)..`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1967, s. 6, for "return the foodgrains or edible oilseeds or edible oils seized" (w.e.f. 30-12-1967).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 92 of 1976, s. 6, for "such person shall be paid".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 36 of 1967, s. 6, for "as if the foodgrains, edible oilseeds or edible oils, as the case may be," (w.e.f. 30-12-1967).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "articles" (w.e.f. 30-12-1967).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "and such price shall be determined in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (3B) of`
  line `section 3 (w.e.f. 30-12-1967).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_d:
  sectionId (17061)
  sectionNo 6D
  orderNo 11
  title `Award of confiscation not to interfere with other punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 1966, s. 3 (w.e.f. 3-9-1966)..`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17061&sectionno=6D&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_6_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[6D. Award of confiscation`
  line `not to interfere with other punishments.--The award of any`
  line `confiscation under this Act by the Collector shall not prevent the infliction of any punishment to`
  line `which the person affected thereby is liable under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_e:
  sectionId (17062)
  sectionNo 6E
  orderNo 12
  title `Bar of jurisdiction in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_e_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 42 of 1986, s. 2, for section 6E (w.e.f. 9-9-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17062&sectionno=6E&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_6_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[6E. Bar of jurisdiction in certain cases.--Whenever any essential commodity is seized in`
  line `pursuance of an order made under section 3 in relation thereto, or any package, covering or receptacle`
  line `in which such essential commodity is found, or any animal, vehicle, vessel or other conveyance used`
  line `in carrying such essential commodity is seized pending confiscation under section 6A, the Collector,`
  line `or, as the case may be, the State Government concerned under section 6C shall have, and,`
  line `notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law for the time being in force, any`
  line `court, tribunal or other authority shall not have, jurisdiction to make orders with regard to the possession, delivery, disposal, release or distribution of such essential commodity, package, covering,`
  line `receptacle, animal, vehicle, vessel or other conveyance.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (17063)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 13
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17063&sectionno=7&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) If any person contravenes any order made under Section 3,--`
  line
  line `(a) he shall be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of an order made with reference to clause (h) or clause (i) of sub-section (2)`
  line `of that section, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year and shall also be`
  line `liable to fine, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of any other order, with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less`
  line `than three months but which may extend to seven years and shall also be liable to fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for any adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment, impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than three months;`
  line
  line `(b) any property in respect of which the order has been contravened shall be forfeited to the`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(c) any package, covering or receptacle in which the property is found and any animal,`
  line `vehicle, vessel or other conveyance used in carrying the property shall, if the court so orders, be`
  line `forfeited to the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person to whom a direction is given under clause (b) of sub-section (4) of section 3 fails`
  line `to comply with the direction, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be`
  line `less than three months but which may extend to seven years and shall also be liable to fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for any adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment, impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than three months.`
  line
  line `(2A) If any person convicted of an offence under sub-clause (ii) of clause (a) of sub-section (1) or`
  line `under sub-section (2) is again convicted of an offence under the same provision, he shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for the second and for every subsequent offence for a term which shall`
  line `not be less than six months but which may extend to seven years and shall also be liable to fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for any adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment, impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than six months.`
  line
  line `(2B) For the purposes of sub-sections (1), (2) and (2A), the fact that an offence under sub-clause`
  line `(ii) of clause (a) of sub-section (1) or under sub-section (2) has caused no substantial harm to the`
  line `general public or to any individual shall be an adequate and special reason for awarding a sentence of`
  line `imprisonment for a term of less than three months or six months, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Where a person having been convicted of an offence under sub-section (1) is again convicted`
  line `convicted of an offence under that sub-section for contravention of an order in respect of an essential`
  line `commodity, the court by which such person is convicted shall, in addition to any penalty which may`
  line `be imposed on him under that sub-section, by order, direct that that person shall not carry on any`
  line `business in that essential commodity for such period, not being less than six months, as may be`
  line `specified by the Court in the Order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 30 of 1974, s. 6, for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 36 of 1967, s. 7 (w.e.f. 30-12-1967).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (17064)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 14
  title `Power of Central Government to recover certain amounts as arrears of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17064&sectionno=7A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[7A. Power of Central Government to recover certain amounts as arrears of land`
  line `revenue.--(1) Where any person, liable to--`
  line
  line `(a) pay any amount in pursuance of any order made under section 3, or`
  line
  line `(b) deposit any amount to the credit of any Account or Fund constituted by or in pursuance of`
  line `any order made under that section,`
  line
  line `makes any default in paying or depositing the whole or any part of such amount, the amount in respect`
  line `of which such default has been made shall [whether such order was made before or after the`
  line `commencement of the Essential Commodities (Amendment) Act, 1984 (34 of 1984), and whether the`
  line `liability of such person to pay or deposit such amount arose before or after such commencement] be`
  line `recoverable by Government together with simple interest due thereon computed at the rate of ^2[fifteen`
  line `per cent.] per annum from the date of such default to the date of recovery of such amount, as an arrear`
  line `of land revenue ^3[or as a public demand].`
  line
  line `(2) The amount recovered under sub-section (1) shall be dealt with in accordance with the order`
  line `under which the liability to pay or deposit such amount arose.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or any`
  line `contract to the contrary, no court, tribunal or other authority shall grant any injunction or make any`
  line `order prohibiting or restraining any Government from recovering any amount as an arrear of land`
  line `revenue ^3[or as a public demand] in pursuance of the provisions of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) If any order, in pursuance of which any amount has been recovered by Government as an`
  line `arrear of land revenue ^3[or as a public demand] under subsection (1) is declared by a competent court,`
  line `after giving to the Government a reasonable opportunity of being heard, to be invalid, the Government`
  line `shall refund the amount so recovered by it to the person from whom it was recovered, together with`
  line `simple interest due thereon, computed at the rate of ^2[fifteen per cent.] per annum, from the date of`
  line `recovery of such amount to the date on which such refund is made.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, Government means the Government by which`
  line `the concerned order under section 3 was made or where such order was made by an officer or`
  line `authority subordinate to any Government, that Government.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 7A in Central Act 10 of 1955.- After section 7 of the Essential Commodities Act, 1955 (Central Act 10 of 1955), in its application to the State of, the following new section shall be inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `"7A. Forfeiture of certain property used in the commission of the offence.-Whenever any offence relating to foodstuffs which is punishable under section 7 has been committed, the Court shall direct that all the packages, coverings or receptacles in which any property liable to be forfeited under the said section is found and all the animals, vehicles, vessels or other conveyances used in carrying the said property shall be forfeited to the Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Court is of opinion that it is not necessary to direct forfeiture in respect of all such packages, coverings or receptacles or such animals, vehicles, vessels or other conveyances or any of them, it may, for reasons to be recorded, refrain from doing so".`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 32 of 1960, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 34 of 1984, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-7-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 42 of 1986, s. 3, for six per cent. (w.e.f. 8-9-1986).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 3, ibid (w.e.f. 8-9-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (17065)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 15
  title `Attempts and abetment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17065&sectionno=8&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Any person who attempts to contravene, or abets a contravention`
  line `of, any order made under section 3 shall be deemed to have contravened that order.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (17066)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 16
  title `False statement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1967, s. 8, for "three years" (w.e.f. 30-12-1967).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17066&sectionno=9&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `If any person,--`
  line
  line `(i) when required by any order made under section 3 to make any statement or furnish any`
  line `information, makes any statement or furnishes any information which is false in any material`
  line `particular and which he knows or has reasonable cause to believe to be false, or does not believe`
  line `to be true, or`
  line
  line `(ii) makes any such statement as aforesaid in any book, account, record, declaration, return or`
  line `other document which he is required by any such order to maintain or furnish,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `^1[five years,] or with fine,`
  line `or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (17067)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 17
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17067&sectionno=10&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person contravening an order made under section 3 is a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the contravention was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company,`
  line `shall be deemed to be guilty of the contravention and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the contravention took place without his knowledge or that he exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent such contravention.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has`
  line `been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent`
  line `or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate, and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (17068)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 18
  title `Offences to be cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17068&sectionno=10A&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Offences to be cognizable.--Notwithstanding anything contained in ^2[the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)] every offence punishable under this Act shall be`
  line `"cognizable ^3`
  line ***].
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1967, s. 9 (w.e.f. 30-12-1967).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 30 of 1974, s. 7, for "the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)" (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
  line
  line `3. The words "and bailable" omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_b:
  sectionId (17069)
  sectionNo 10B
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of court to publish name, place of business, etc., of companies convicted under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17069&sectionno=10B&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[10B. Power of court to publish name, place of business, etc., of companies convicted under`
  line `the Act.--(1) Where any company is convicted under this Act, it shall be competent for the court`
  line `convicting the company to cause the name and place of business of the company, nature of the`
  line `contravention, the fact that the company has been so convicted and such other particulars as the court`
  line `may consider to be appropriate in the circumstances of the case, to be published at the expense of the`
  line `company in such newspapers or in such other manner as the court may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) No publication under sub-section (1) shall be made until the period for preferring an appeal`
  line `against the orders of the court has expired without any appeal having been preferred, or such an`
  line `appeal, having been preferred, has been disposed of.`
  line
  line `(3) The expenses of any publication under sub-section (1) shall be recoverable from the company`
  line `as if it were a fine imposed by the court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "company" has the meaning assigned to it in`
  line `clause (a) of the Explanation of section 10.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_c:
  sectionId (17070)
  sectionNo 10C
  orderNo 20
  title `Presumption of culpable mental state.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17070&sectionno=10C&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_10_c_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any prosecution for any offence under this`
  line `Act which requires a culpable mental state on the part of the accused, the court shall presume the`
  line `existence of such mental state but it shall be a defence for the accused to prove the fact that he had no`
  line `such mental state with respect to the act charged as an offence in that prosecution.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "culpable mental state" includes intention, motive, knowledge of a`
  line `fact and the belief in, or reason to believe, a fact.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, a fact is said to be proved only when the court believes it to`
  line `exist beyond reasonable doubt and not merely when its existence is established by a preponderance of`
  line probability.]
obj_root_law_sections_10_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (17071)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 21
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17071&sectionno=11&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `No Court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under`
  line `this Act except on a report in writing of the facts constituting such offence made by a person who is a`
  line `public servant as defined in section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of I860) ^1[or any person`
  line `aggrieved or any recognised consumer association, whether such person is a member of that`
  line `association or not].`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.--For the purposes of this section and section 12AA, "recognised consumer`
  line `association" means a voluntary consumer association registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of`
  line `1956) or any other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 73 of 1986, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-5-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Added by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-5-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (17072)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 22
  title `Special provision regarding fine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 30 of 1974, s. 9 (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17072&sectionno=12&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Special provision regarding fine.--Notwithstanding anything contained in section 29 of`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), it shall be lawful for any Metropolitan Magistrate,`
  line `or any Judicial Magistrate of the first class specially empowered by the State Government in this behalf, to pass a sentence of fine exceeding five thousand rupees on any person convicted of`
  line `contravening any order made under section 3.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (17073)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to try summarily.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17073&sectionno=12A&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Power to try summarily.--(1) If the Central Government is of opinion that a situation has`
  line `arisen where, in the interests of production, supply or distribution of ^2[any essential commodity not`
  line `being an essential commodity referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (2)] or trade or commerce therein`
  line `and other relevant considerations, it is necessary that the contravention of any order made under`
  line `section 3 in relation to such essential commodity should be tried summarily, the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify such order to be a special order for purposes of`
  line `summary trial under this section, and every such notification shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `issued, before both Houses of Parliament:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) every such notification issued after the commencement of the Essential Commodities`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1971, shall, unless sooner rescinded, cease to operate at the expiration of two`
  line `years after the publication of such notification in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(b) every such notification in force immediately before such commencement shall, unless`
  line `sooner rescinded, cease to operate at the expiration of two years after such commencement:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in the foregoing proviso shall affect any case relating to the`
  line `contravention of a special order specified in any such notification if proceedings by way of summary`
  line `trial have commenced before that notification is rescinded or ceases to operate and the provisions of`
  line `this section shall continue to apply to that case as if that notification had not been rescinded or had not`
  line `ceased to operate.]`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)`
  line `all, offences relating to--`
  line
  line `(a) the contravention of an order made under section 3 with respect to--`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(ii) foodstuffs, including edible oilseeds and oil; or`
  line
  line `(iii) drugs; and`
  line
  line `(b) where any notification issued under sub-section (1) in relation to a special order is in`
  line `force, the contravention of such special order,`
  line
  line `shall be tried in a summary way by a Judicial Magistrate of the First Class specially empowered in`
  line `this behalf by the State Government or by a Metropolitan Magistrate and the provisions of sections`
  line `262 to 265 (both inclusive) of the said Code shall, as far as may be, apply to such trial:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the case of any conviction in a summary trial under this section, it shall be lawful`
  line `for the Magistrate to pass a sentence of imprisonment for a term not exceeding one year:`
  line
  line `Provided further that when at the commencement of, or in the course of, a summary trial under`
  line `this section, it appears to the Magistrate that the nature of the case is such that a sentence of`
  line `imprisonment for a term exceeding one year may have to be passed or that it is, for any other reason,`
  line `undesirable to try the case summarily, the Magistrate shall, after hearing the parties, record an order`
  line `to that effect and thereafter recall any witnesses who may have been examined and proceed to hear or`
  line `re-hear the case in the manner provided by the said Code.]`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in ^6[the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974),] there shall be no appeal by a convicted person in any case tried summarily under this section in which the Magistrate passes a sentence of imprisonment not exceeding one`
  line `month, ^7[and of fine not exceeding two thousand rupees] whether or not any order of forfeiture of`
  line `property or an order under ^8[section 452] of the said Code is made in addition to such sentences, but`
  line `an appeal shall lie where any sentence ^9*** in excess of the aforesaid limits is passed by the`
  line Magistrate.
  line
  line `^10[(4) All cases relating to the contravention of an order referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (2),`
  line `not being a special order, and pending before a Magistrate immediately before the commencement of`
  line `the Essential Commodities (Amendment) Act, 1974, and, where any notification is issued under subsection`
  line `(1) in relation to a special order, all cases relating to the contravention of such special order`
  line `and pending before a Magistrate immediately before the date of the issue of such notification, shall, if`
  line `no witnesses have been examined before such commencement or the said date, as the case may be, be`
  line `tried in a summary way under this section, and if any such case is pending before a Magistrate who is`
  line `not competent to try the same in a summary way under this section, it shall be forwarded to a`
  line `Magistrate so competent./]br`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 1964, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 30 of 1974, s. 10, for "any essential commodity" (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
  line
  line `3. Added by Act 66 of 1971, s. 5 (w.e.f. 23-12-1971).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 30 of 1974, s. 10, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
  line
  line `5. Sub-clause (i) omitted by Act 54 of 2006, s. 5 (w.e.f. 12-2-2007).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 30 of 1974, s. 10, for "the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)" (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 30 of 1974, s. 10, for "or of fine not exceeding two thousand rupees or both" (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "section 517" (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
  line
  line `9. The words "of imprisonment or fine" omitted by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_b:
  sectionId (17074)
  sectionNo 12B
  orderNo 24
  title `Grant of injunction, etc., by civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-6-1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17074&sectionno=12B&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[12B. Grant of injunction, etc., by civil courts.--No civil court shall grant an injunction or`
  line `make any order for any other relief, against the Central Government or any State Government or a`
  line `Public officer in respect of any Act done or purporting to be done by such Government, or such`
  line `officer in his official capacity, under this Act or any order made thereunder, until after notice of the`
  line `application for such injunction or other relief has been given to such Government or officer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (17075)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 25
  title `Presumption as to orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17075&sectionno=13&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Where an order purports to have been made and signed by an`
  line `authority in exercise of any power conferred by or under this Act, a court shall presume that such`
  line `order was so made by that authority within the meaning of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (17076)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 26
  title `Burden of proof in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17076&sectionno=14&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Where a person is prosecuted for contravening any order`
  line `made under section 3 which prohibits him from doing any act or being in possession of a thing`
  line `without lawful authority or without a permit, licence or other document, the burden of proving that he`
  line `has such authority, permit, licence or other document shall be on him.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (17077)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 27
  title `Protection of action taken under Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17077&sectionno=15&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in`
  line `pursuance of any order made under section 3.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Government for any damage caused or`
  line `likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of any`
  line `order made under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (17078)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 28
  title `Prosecution of public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 92 of 1976, s. 8 (w.e.f. 2-9-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17078&sectionno=15A&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Prosecution of public servants.--Where any person who is a public servant is accused of`
  line `of any offence alleged to have been committed by him while acting or purporting to act in the`
  line `discharge of his duty in pursuance of an order made under section 3, no court shall take cognizance of`
  line `such offence except with the previous sanction--`
  line
  line `(a) of the Central Government, in the case of a person who is employed or, as the case may`
  line `be, was at the time of commission of the alleged offence employed, in connection with the affairs`
  line `of the Union;`
  line
  line `(b) of the State Government, in the case of a person who is employed or, as the case may be,`
  line `was at the time of commission of the alleged offence employed, in connection with the affairs of`
  line `the State.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (17079)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 29
  title `Repeals and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439&sectionId=17079&sectionno=16&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00003_195510_1517807320439
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following laws are hereby repealed:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Essential Commodities Ordinance, 1955 (1 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(b) any other law in force in any State immediately before the commencement of this Act in`
  line `so far as such law controls or authorises the control of the production, supply and distribution of,`
  line `and trade and commerce in, any essential commodity.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, any order made or deemed to be made by any authority`
  line `whatsoever, under any law repealed hereby and in force immediately before the commencement of`
  line `this Act, shall, in so far as such order may be made under this Act, be deemed to be made under this`
  line `Act and continue in force, and accordingly any appointment made, licence or permit granted or`
  line `direction issued under any such order and in force immediately before such commencement shall`
  line `continue in force until and unless it is superseded by any appointment made, licence or permit granted`
  line `or direction issued under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The provision of sub-section (2) shall be without prejudice to the provision contained in`
  line `section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), which shall also apply to the repeal of the`
  line `Ordinance or other law referred to in sub-section (1) as if such Ordinance or other law had been an`
  line enactment.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
